              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ASEP",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Sample of metal and oxide 238U and 15%",
                "233U were irradiated at various fluxes and",
                "irradiation times in Chalk River reactor. Associated",
                "with samples were one or more 0.127 mm cobalt wires",
                "weighing 1.148 mg. The cobalt standard was calibrated",
                "by coincidence and 4pi counting techniques. The",
                "thermal fluxes were calculated from the observed",
                "activity after corrections assuming a value of 36.5",
                "barns for 2,200 m/sec cross section of 59Co. The mass",
                "spectrometry was carried out using a Nier-type",
                "spectrometer of 25 cm radius with an all metal tube."
              ]
            }
          ],
